Keys To Understanding Poetry

Poetry is a Written And Oral Tradition composed of rhythimcal words
describing an expereince or something of ones Imagination In a way deemed beautiful
and more concentrated than ordinary speech

Spoken Sound

Poetry makes us happyier and sadder and more alive

poetry is the creaion amaginarion and life

KEY#1: You dont have to like it, but you do have to give it a chance

KEY#2: Think of poetry as a different way to look at the world

KEY#3: Break a poem up into small bite-sized nuggets for easier understanding

KEY#4: Annotate

KEY#5: Identifi the narrator

KEY#6: Notice "shifts" or key 
